# COMP.SEC.300 Secure CRUD API

This project is a secure programming demonstration API for managing users. It was developed for the COMP.SEC.300 Secure Programming course as a small seminar-style project. The application demonstrates secure user registration, login, logout, cookie-based JWT authentication, protected routes, input validation, password hashing, safe API responses, and Swagger-based manual security testing.

The goal of the project is not only to build a working CRUD API, but also to show how secure programming principles can be applied in a real backend application.

---

## 1. Main Features

* User registration
* User login and logout
* Current authenticated user endpoint
* Protected user routes
* Password hashing with bcrypt
* JWT authentication
* Signed HttpOnly cookie storage
* Input validation with Joi
* MariaDB database using TypeORM
* Swagger/OpenAPI documentation
* Manual security testing through Swagger
* Safe response mapping to avoid exposing sensitive data

