### Folder and File Description

`src/index.ts` is the main entry point of the application. It creates the Fastify server, connects to the database, registers plugins, enables Swagger documentation, and registers the API routes.

`src/data-source.ts` contains the TypeORM database configuration. It reads environment variables and connects the application to the MariaDB database.

`src/api/auth.ts` contains authentication-related routes such as login, logout, and checking the currently authenticated user through `/auth/me`.

`src/api/user.ts` contains user-related routes such as creating users and retrieving user data.

`src/entity/User.ts` defines the User entity used by TypeORM. This entity represents the user table in the MariaDB database.

`src/plugin/authenticate.ts` contains the authentication plugin. It verifies the signed JWT cookie before allowing access to protected routes.

`src/types/user.ts` contains TypeScript types related to users, login data, JWT payloads, and safe user responses.

`src/utils/cookies.ts` contains the authentication cookie name and cookie security options.

`src/utils/mapUser.ts` contains the `toSafeUser` function. This function converts a database user entity into a safe response object without exposing sensitive fields such as `passwordHash`.

`src/utils/validators.ts` contains Joi validation schemas for password rules, user creation, login, and user ID validation.

