## 14. Database Commands

Login to MariaDB inside the Docker container:

```bash
docker exec -it compsec300-db mariadb -u root -p
```

Enter root password:

```txt
my-secret-pw
```

Select the database:

```sql
USE `compsec300-db`;
```

Show tables:

```sql
SHOW TABLES;
```

View all users:

```sql
SELECT id, email, username, role FROM `user`;
```

View one user:

```sql
SELECT email, username, role
FROM `user`
WHERE email = 'user1@example.com';
```

Change a user role:

```sql
UPDATE `user`
SET role = 'admin'
WHERE email = 'admin@example.com';
```

Delete all users:

```sql
DELETE FROM `user`;
```

Reset the user table:

```sql
TRUNCATE TABLE `user`;
```

If the table name is `users` instead of `user`, replace `user` with `users` in the SQL commands.

