## 16. Security Notes

This project demonstrates several secure programming principles:

* Validate input before processing it
* Enforce password complexity
* Hash passwords before storing them
* Use JWT for authentication
* Store JWT in a signed HttpOnly cookie
* Protect sensitive routes with an authentication pre-handler
* Return safe user objects instead of full database entities
* Avoid exposing `passwordHash` in API responses
* Use TypeORM repository methods instead of raw SQL string concatenation
* Use Swagger to manually test validation and authentication behavior

One important improvement is authorization. The current `/users` route checks whether the user is authenticated, but it may also need role-based access control. In a production system, retrieving all users should normally be restricted to admin users only.

